title: Show returns with tons of fun
text:
2015 Geelong Show rolls into city with animals, showbags galore by: What are these? Leopold’s Maggie Patmore, 12, with showdog Archie. Picture: Glenn Ferguson Source: News Limited 
MORE than 200 different showbags will be available when the Royal Geelong Show rolls into the city next week. 
Victoria’s largest regional show begins on October 15, with gamers, sports fans and sweet tooths to be spoiled for choice. 
Leopold’s Maggie Patmore said it was the laughs, not the lollies, inside the showbags that made the show an annual highlight. 
“This will be my seventh time at the show,” she said. 
“I like the joke showbags where you get all different pranks and fun stuff.” 
Harry’s Farmyard and a selection of reptiles will be returning to delight animal lovers of all ages. 
Mahli Chisholm, 6, who said the chance to make some fury friends is the best part of the day. 
“I like the cows the best because my nickname is Moo,” she said. 
Monster trucks, motor cross, pig racing and Australia’s largest interactive travelling fishing show will also entertain showgoers across the four days. 
Vintage machinery and an abundance of agricultural stalls will provide an insight into the history of farming and a spectacular firework display will take place on Friday and Saturday evening. 
— The Geelong News is giving away 25 family passes to the show. Entry details are included in the October 7 edition of the free weekly newspaper.
